    <text type="correspondence">
        <body>
            <div1>
                <pb facs="ccda.corr000206.001.jpg"/>

                <fw type="letterhead" place="top-right" hand="#h03">1005 Williamson Building<lb/>Cleveland,
                    O.</fw>
                    
                <dateline><date when="1902-08-16">Aug 16, 1902.</date></dateline>


                <opener>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Horace L. Traubel, Esq.,</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Camden, N.J.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>My dear Mr. Traubel:&#8212;<ref type="editorial" resp="#slg" n="1"
                            target="#Traub"/>
                    </salute>
                </opener>

                <p hand="#h03">I have been intending for sometime to put the "Conservator"<ref type="editorial" resp="#slg" target="#Conserv"/> on the list of magazines which come to my house. It sounds a high clear note in favor of Truth and Justice and Civic Righteousness, which ought to be an doubtless is heard by many thousands, to whom I wish to be added. Will you kindly transmit the enclosed money order to the business <choice><orig>man-</orig><reg>management</reg></choice>
                    
                    <pb facs="ccda.corr000206.001.jpg"/><choice><orig>agement</orig><reg/></choice> &amp; request that the Conservator be sent to<lb/>"Chas. W. Chesnutt<lb/>64 Brenton St.<lb/>Cleveland, O."</p>
                
                <p>Permit me to assure you still further of my full appreciation of the kind things you have said about my books &amp;for your kindly interest in &amp; support of the cause which they have been written to promote.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely yours,</salute>
                    <signed hand="#h03">Chas. W. Chesnutt.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>

