                <note>Horace Traubel was an American poet, essayist, and author. Traubel was also a dedicated Socialist, and one of the founders of the socialist weekly newspaper <hi rend="italic">The Worker</hi>. He is best known for being Whitman's literary executor and author of a nine-volume biography of hitman's final four years (1888-1892), entitled <hi rend="italic">Walt Whitman in Camden</hi>.</note>
                <note n="1">This is one of the earliest letters that Chesnutt send Traubel. The two men had a friendly working relationship; Chesnutt was a fan of the magazine that Traubel founded, <hi rend="italic">The Conservator</hi>, and Traubel consistently praised Chesnutt and his writing in reviews featured in his periodical.</note>
            </person>
        </listPerson>

